line_1: The Printers may, indeed, be starv'd.

line_1: And dealing honestly, was almost starv'd.
line_2: I for this Conduct had what I deserv'd;

line_1: Nor prais'd by whom she's over-reach'd or starv'd.
line_2: Silent and meek she passes unobserv'd,

line_1: Eats not on silver, while his train are starv'd;
Admir'd, repuls'd! just pity'd, prais'd, and starv'd!
